President Barack Obama has declared October 2013 as National Arts and Humanities Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of arts and humanities in shaping American society and culture. He emphasizes how works of art, literature, music, and other creative expressions have the power to open minds, nourish souls, and deepen our understanding of what it means to be human and American. The proclamation also emphasizes the need to support and nurture the talents of young people in the arts and humanities, alongside the development of skills in critical thinking and creativity. The President calls upon the people of the United States to observe this month by celebrating and participating in activities that promote and honor the arts and humanities.